-- Accused Spy Vicky Pelaez's Bail Will Be Appealed by Prosecutors in N.Y.
-- Bob Van Voris
-- 2010-07-06T20:04:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/accused-spy-vicky-pelaez-s-bail-will-be-appealed-by-prosecutors-in-n-y-.html

          
          
             U.S. prosecutors in New York said
they will appeal a magistrate’s decision granting bail to Vicky
Pelaez, one of 11 people charged in an alleged ‘deep-cover’
Russian spy ring. U.S. Magistrate Judge Ronald Ellis granted
$250,000 bail to Pelaez, who hasn’t yet been released from
custody.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
